Description.value:
ABT JIRA iFlow delivers sample interface for creating tickets in JIRA. Sprint Variable of JIRA is externalized and can be maintained by the user or mapped to the API request for eg. In the sample ABT iFlow, customField_10020 is mapped to JIRA field Sprint. The sprint field must be adjusted as per your JIRA APIs. Contact support@abusinesstech.com for any issues or queries with this sample iFlow.

(XML Schema is provided below).

<JIRATicket>
	<Action>CREATE</Action>
	<ProjectId>12345</ProjectId>
	<Summary>SnowTicket handler | </Summary>
	<Description>Bad Request : 400 : HTTP/1.1 Grouping BP01 has external number assignment, enter a number</Description>
	<Assignee>undefined</Assignee>
	<IssueType>Bug</IssueType>
	<SprintNum>1137</SprintNum>
	<Reporter>dostaddon</Reporter>
</JIRATicket>
